esulting in less agitation than if setting large side up)  so the best way to keep it is on it's side slightly pointing down, so the entire cork is kept moist, but not under the pressure of the entire contents, turned every year or so (the darker the wine, the more often you would want to turn it) to prevent accumulation of sediment and to rotate the corks.<br>
<br>
The rotation of wines is usually done on a bi-annual process in major warehouses of wines, usually coinsiding with a tasting party, (free labor &amp; promotion from all attendees) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=30057"><br>
